                    type: "singleCorrect",
                    html: 'Match List I with List II<table border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width: 500px;"> <tbody> <tr> <td colspan="2" rowspan="1" style="text-align: center;"><strong>LIST-I<br/>\t\t\tComplex</strong></td> <td colspan="2" rowspan="1" style="text-align: center;"><strong>LIST-II<br/>\t\t\tColour</strong></td> </tr> <tr> <td style="text-align: center;">A.</td> <td style="text-align: center;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>Mg</mi><mfenced><msub><mi>NH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></mfenced><msub><mi>PO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math></td> <td style="text-align: center;">I.</td> <td style="text-align: center;">brown</td> </tr> <tr> <td style="text-align: center;">B.</td> <td style="text-align: center;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mi mathvariant="normal">K</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mfenced close="]" open="["><mrow><mi>Co</mi><msub><mfenced><msub><mi>NO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>6</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced></math></td> <td style="text-align: center;">II.</td> <td style="text-align: center;">white</td> </tr> <tr> <td style="text-align: center;">C.</td> <td style="text-align: center;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>MnO</mi><msub><mfenced><mi>OH</mi></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msub></math></td> <td style="text-align: center;">III.</td> <td style="text-align: center;">yellow</td> </tr> <tr> <td style="text-align: center;">D.</td> <td style="text-align: center;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mi>Fe</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><msub><mfenced close="]" open="["><mrow><mi>Fe</mi><msub><mfenced><mi>CN</mi></mfenced><mn>6</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msub></math></td> <td style="text-align: center;">IV.</td> <td style="text-align: center;">blue</td> </tr> </tbody></table><p>Choose the correct answer from the options given below:</p>',
                    sol: '<p>The formula <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>Mg</mi><mo>(</mo><msub><mi>NH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>)</mo><msub><mi>PO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math> represents magnesium ammonium phosphate it is white in colour.\u00a0<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mi mathvariant="normal">K</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mfenced close="]" open="["><mrow><mi>Co</mi><msub><mfenced><msub><mi>NO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>6</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced></math>\u00a0is known as potassium hexanitritocobaltate(III). It is yellow in colour. The yellow colour is due to the presence of the cobalt ion (Co3+) in the complex, which absorbs certain wavelengths of light and reflects yellow light.\u00a0\u00a0<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>MnO</mi><msub><mfenced><mi>OH</mi></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msub></math>is brown in colour.\u00a0<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mi>Fe</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><msub><mfenced close="]" open="["><mrow><mi>Fe</mi><msub><mfenced><mi>CN</mi></mfenced><mn>6</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msub></math>\u00a0is blue in colour.\u00a0</p><table border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width: 500px;"> <tbody> <tr> <td style="text-align: center;">Complex</td> <td style="text-align: center;">Colour</td> </tr> <tr> <td style="text-align: center;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>Mg</mi><mfenced><msub><mi>NH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></mfenced><msub><mi>PO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math></td> <td style="text-align: center;">White\u00a0</td> </tr> <tr> <td style="text-align: center;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mi mathvariant="normal">K</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mfenced close="]" open="["><mrow><mi>Co</mi><msub><mfenced><msub><mi>NO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>6</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced></math></td> <td style="text-align: center;">Yellow</td> </tr> <tr> <td style="text-align: center;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>MnO</mi><msub><mfenced><mi>OH</mi></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msub></math></td> <td style="text-align: center;">Brown</td> </tr> <tr> <td style="text-align: center;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mi>Fe</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><msub><mfenced close="]" open="["><mrow><mi>Fe</mi><msub><mfenced><mi>CN</mi></mfenced><mn>6</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msub></math></td> <td style="text-align: center;">Blue</td> </tr> </tbody></table>',
