                    sol: '<p>The dimension of magnetic induction is,\u00a0<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msup><mi>MT</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">A</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>, the dimension of magnetic flux is,\u00a0<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>\u03d5</mi><mo>=</mo><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>\u2192</mo></mover><mo>\u00b7</mo><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>\u2192</mo></mover><mo>\u21d2</mo><mfenced close="]" open="["><mi>\u03d5</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>ML</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mrow><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">A</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>,\u00a0the dimension of magnetic permeability,\u00a0<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msup><mi>MLT</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">A</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>\u00a0and, the dimension of magnetization,\u00a0<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">M</mi><mn>0</mn></msup><msup><mrow><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">L</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">A</mi></math>.</p>',
