                    html: "Which of the following compound CANNOT act as a Lewis base?",
                    sol: '<p>Lewis base: Chemical species which has capability to donate electron pair.</p><p>In <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mi>NF</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><msub><mi>SF</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><msub><mi>ClF</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math> central atom (i.e. <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi mathvariant="normal">N</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">S</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>Cl</mi></math>)<br/>having lone pair therefore act as Lewis base.</p><p>In <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mi>PCl</mi><mn>5</mn></msub><mo>,</mo></math>\u00a0central atom <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfenced><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mfenced></math> does not have lone pair therefore does not act as Lewis base.</p>',
