                    type: "singleCorrect",
                    html: "Incorrect statement for the use of indicator in acid-base titration is:",
                    sol: "<p>Methyl orange and phenolphthalein\u00a0indicators work with the change in pH and are termed as acid\u2013base\u00a0indicators.</p><p>Methy lorange is sutable indicator for strong acid vs strong base and strong acid vs weak base titration.</p><p>Phenolphthalein is sutable indicator for strong acid vs strong base and weak acid vs strong base titration.</p><p>There is no suitable indicator that can be used in the titration of weak acid and weak base. So, the correct option is A.</p>",
