                    html: 'A block of mass <math><mi>m</mi><mo>,</mo></math> lying on a smooth horizontal surface, is attached to a spring (of negligible mass) of spring constant <math><mi>k</mi><mo>.</mo></math> The other end of the spring is fixed, as shown in the figure. The block is initially at rest in its equilibrium position. If now the block is pulled with a constant force <math><mi>F</mi><mo>,</mo></math> the maximum speed of the block is:</p><img src="https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq_book_2024/gkvndhgfanlffeeyiwvnmuwttbylfqtrpnkjygclvmgynvyjiq.png"/>',
                    sol: '<img alt="" src="https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq_book_2024/399792_figure_1.png" style="width: 237px; height: 95px;"/><br/>When block attains maximum speed net force on <math><mi>m</mi></math> is zero. <math><mo>\u2234</mo><mi>F</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></math><br/>Or <math><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>k</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br/>From work energy theorem<br/><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>\u00a0</mi><mi>k</mi><mi>\u00a0</mi><msup><mfenced separators="|"><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mi>k</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>F</mi><mfenced separators="|"><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mi>k</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msubsup><mi>V</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">a</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">x</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></msubsup></math><br/><math><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msubsup><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">a</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup></math><br/><math><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">a</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">x</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math>',
